  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-001",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "callout",
    "text": "Working draft â€” do not circulate â€” S.L. comments in brackets. Snapshot frozen 2026-02-18 for committee reference; supersede only with a new snapshot, not silent edits.",
    "order": "1",
    "created_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-010",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "heading_2",
    "text": "3.1 Study system and sites",
    "order": "2",
    "created_time": "2026-01-28T14:20:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-011",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Between July and October 2025 I surveyed three focal sites along the southern Puget Sound thermal gradient [S.L.: confirm the end-of-season window is defensible if Marcus asks]. The three-site framing keeps the design tractable while spanning the temperature range we care about.",
    "order": "3",
    "created_time": "2026-01-28T14:22:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-012",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Dash Point anchors the cool end of the gradient at 13.9Â°C mean summer surface temperature, and Owen Beach anchors the warm end at 16.3Â°C, giving roughly a 2.4Â°C spread across the focal set. Titlow Beach sits in the middle as the most heavily instrumented site.",
    "order": "4",
    "created_time": "2026-01-28T14:24:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-020",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "heading_2",
    "text": "3.2 Mytilus trossulus dynamics",
    "order": "5",
    "created_time": "2026-01-30T15:00:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-021",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Percent cover of Mytilus trossulus at Titlow Beach declined from 61% in the coolest visit to 44% at the warmest, an absolute drop of 17 percentage points across the Julyâ€“October 2025 window [S.L.: strong headline result, keep the framing].",
    "order": "6",
    "created_time": "2026-01-30T15:02:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-030",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "heading_2",
    "text": "3.3 Predator and grazer counts",
    "order": "7",
    "created_time": "2026-02-02T11:30:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-031",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Pisaster ochraceus counts ranged from 1 to 6 individuals per transect across the visits, with the peak count observed at Titlow Beach during the July survey.",
    "order": "8",
    "created_time": "2026-02-02T11:32:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-032",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Tegula funebralis appeared consistently at Titlow Beach across the season, averaging 18 individuals per transect during the October 2025 survey and providing a mid-trophic grazer signal that tracks the warming trend [S.L.: Tegula this far north is a stretch â€” double-check the taxonomic ID before this leaves the room].",
    "order": "9",
    "created_time": "2026-02-05T09:45:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-040",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "heading_2",
    "text": "3.4 Warming context and figure 3.4",
    "order": "10",
    "created_time": "2026-02-10T16:10:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-041",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Figure 3.4 plots the trailing 12-month sea-surface temperature anomaly against the 1985â€“2010 baseline pulled from the NASA SST monthly-mean series (pre-2024 pipeline). The chapter figure references the anomaly value that came out of the pre-2024 baseline extraction [S.L.: the pre-2024 baseline is fine for the frozen draft, we can revisit if the new pipeline shifts the anchor].",
    "order": "11",
    "created_time": "2026-02-10T16:12:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-050",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "heading_2",
    "text": "3.5 Statistical footprint",
    "order": "12",
    "created_time": "2026-02-14T10:30:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
    "checked": "true"
  },
  {
    "id": "block-fc-051",
    "page_id": "page-th-chapter3-frozen-2026-02-18",
    "parent_block_id": "-13",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Regression of percent cover on mean site temperature gives RÂ² = 0.21; a PERMANOVA on community composition returns p = 0.018; NMDS ordination produced a stress value of 0.14. All analyses run in R 4.4.1 with vegan. Ordination is at siteâ€“visit level in this snapshot (Brayâ€“Curtis).",
    "order": "13",
    "created_time": "2026-02-14T10:32:00.000Z",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T09:14:00.000Z",
    "has_children": "false",
